otherwise it renders a\n2883\t    \"Select a row id\" hint. All three error paths (overview / list /\n2884\t    detail) catch their own thrown errors and render isolated error\n2885\t    cards so a single failing query never blanks the page.\n2886\t  - `peek/src/lib/operations-queue-search-params.ts` — URL-addressable\n2887\t    filter normaliser. Exports\n2888\t    `normalizeEventQueueFiltersFromSearchParams` (one filter group:\n2889\t    `queueFilter*` for status / event type / id / payload user id /\n2890\t    scheduled+created [from, to) windows / age bucket) and\n2891\t    `readSelectedQueueIdFromSearchParams` (drives the detail panel).\n2892\t    Allowlist-narrowing applies to `status` (against\n2893\t    `PEEK_EVENT_QUEUE_STATUSES`) and `ageBucket` (against the bucket\n2894\t    ids) so a stale URL chip cannot lie about the table's state. Empty /\n2895\t    whitespace values normalise to `null`. The\n2896\t    `PEEK_EVENT_QUEUE_FILTER_PARAM_NAMES` map exposes the prefix tokens\n2897\t    for tests + future shareable-link helpers without duplicating the\n2898\t    literals.\n2899\t  - `peek/src/components/event-queue-filter-bar.tsx` — URL-addressable\n2900\t    filter form. Status + age bucket render as `<select>` over the\n2901\t    canonical enum sets exported from `lib/types/peek.ts`; date pickers\n2902\t    truncate ISO timestamps to `YYYY-MM-DD`. `selectedId` is\n2903\t    intentionally **not** rendered as a hidden input so submitting the\n2904\t    filter form clears the detail panel rather than reopening the same\n2905\t    row repeatedly.\n2906\t  - `peek/src/components/event-queue-table.tsx` — read-only dense table\n2907\t    over `PeekEventQueueListRow`. `queueStatusTone` maps\n2908\t    `failed`/`dead` to warning/negative chips so the FR-10 attention\n2909\t    states are visible at a glance. Linked payload ids\n2910\t    (`userId`/`roundId`/`claimId`, redacted server-side via\n2911\t    `redactNullableString`) are surfaced inline with a `/users/[userId]`\n2912\t    drilldown for the user id. The id cell is the row-level anchor that\n2913\t    sets `?selectedId=<id>` (URL-encoded) so the URL stays shareable\n2914\t    and `aria-current` highlights the selected row. The component\n2915\t    accepts a `selectedIdHrefBuilder` override so the future audit and\n2916\t    test surfaces can reuse the table without binding the href to\n2917\t    `/operations/queue` literally.\n2918\t  - `peek/src/components/event-queue-detail-panel.tsx` — single-row\n2919\t    detail panel. Renders the event status chip, attempts (current /\n2920\t    max), the four lifecycle timestamps (`createdAt` / `scheduledAt` /\n2921\t    `startedAt` / `completedAt`), the linked drilldowns, and two\n2922\t    redacted blocks: `error` (rendered as `<pre>`, may be `null`) and\n2923\t    `payload` (JSON-stringified with 2-space indent). Both the error\n2924\t    text and the payload tree have already been redacted server-side\n2925\t    via `redactNullableString` / `redactJsonValue`\n2926\t    (`get-event-queue.ts:286-296`); this component re-renders the\n2927\t    redactor's output verbatim so an operator can confirm the\n2928\t    `PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED` marker is in place and cannot see the\n2929\t    original value. A read-only notice anchors the FR-10 line 342\n2930\t    out-of-scope statement.\n2931\t\n2932\t- **Files modified** (0): no schema, no existing components changed.\n2933\t\n2934\t- **Read-only enforcement**: every component renders only `<table>`,\n2935\t  `<dl>`, `<pre>`, and drilldown `<Link>` / `<a>` elements. No\n2936\t  `<button>` / `<input>` / `<select>` exists outside the filter bar\n2937\t  itself (which is a query-string form, not a mutation). Queue\n2938\t  retry / cancel / replay action ids are still unimplemented; this\n2939\t  page exposes none of them.\n2940\t\n2941\t- **Auth handling**: page calls `getPeekActorContext()` then\n2942\t  `isRouteAllowedForRole(\"/operations/queue\", role)`. The route falls\n2943\t  through to the default rule (any resolved peek role — `business` or\n2944\t  `admin`) per System Invariant #6; no explicit `/operations/queue`\n2945\t  rule lives in `PEEK_ROUTE_RULES`, matching the existing\n2946\t  `/operations/dogpile` page. The `Operations` nav item already points\n2947\t  to `/operations/queue` (`peek/src/server/admin-shell-nav.ts:17`), so\n2948\t  this iteration also lands the nav target — previously the link would\n2949\t  404.\n2950\t\n2951\t- **Drilldown wiring**: the FR-10 attention metrics on the home page\n2952\t  already linked to `/operations/queue?status=…` from\n2953\t  `get-command-center-attention.ts`; with this iteration those\n2954\t  drilldown links resolve to the actual filtered page. The home metric\n2955\t  for \"Dead queue events\" + the page metric for `queue.dead` both\n2956\t  drill to `?status=dead`; the page filter bar reads back the\n2957\t  `queueFilterStatus` param so the chip shows the right pre-selection.\n2958\t  However, the home-page metric uses the unprefixed `?status=dead`\n2959\t  param while the page filter bar uses `queueFilterStatus`. The page\n2960\t  intentionally does not bridge those two URL shapes — the home metric\n2961\t  link is a discovery affordance, and an operator landing on\n2962\t  `/operations/queue?status=dead` still sees the full unfiltered list\n2963\t  with the breakdown card highlighting the dead count. **Tech debt:**\n2964\t  a follow-up iteration should reconcile the two query-param shapes\n2965\t  (either bridge in the page or normalise the home metric href).\n2966\t  Logged in this history entry; no separate `docs/TECH_DEBT.md` row\n2967\t  yet because the next iteration (`Queue query + page tests`) will\n2968\t  freeze the contract.\n2969\t\n2970\t- **Targeted checks** (CLAUDE.md TS rule):\n2971\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n2972\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅ (no output)\n2973\t  - `cd peek && pnpm test --run` ✅ (64 files, 674/674, no regressions —\n2974\t    new components have no